criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  present a muscle-skeletal dysfunction, such as osteoporosis, arthritis, tendinitis,
             but being able to perform their ADL without help from others;

          -  did not practice physical activity for at least 12 months;

          -  provide a normal IGF-1 level for their age;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  elderly women unfit to perform the strength and functional autonomy tests for the
             medical assessment;
